-3|x| &= 4x + 1\\
\Rightarrow \qquad -3x &= 4x + 1\\
\Rightarrow \qquad -7x &= 1\\
\Rightarrow \qquad x &= -\frac{1}{7}
\end{align*}We can also factor the left-hand side of the equation as $-3x$ if $x$ is positive and $-3x$ if $x$ is negative.  Now, we have  \begin{align*}
